  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">TO SUPPORT A NEW GOVERNMENT OF AFGHANISTAN (GOA) SCHEME TO ENABLE MINISTRIES AND ?AGENCIES TO RECRUIT ADDITIONAL QUALIFIED STAFF TO LINE MANAGEMENT POSITIONS IN ORDER TO ?IMPROVE PERFORMANCE IN KEY FUNCTIONAL AREAS SUCH AS HUMAN RESOURCE MANAGEMENT, ?PROCUREMENT AND POLICY FORMULATION.  THE MANAGEMENT CAPACITY PROGRAMME (MCP) ?IS FUNDED THROUGH THE ARTF, AND MANAGED DIRECTLY BY THE INDEPENDENT ?ADMINISTRATIVE REFORM AND CIVIL SERVICE COMMISSION (IARCSC). MCP WILL ALSO ?PROVIDE SUPPORT TO THE IARCSC TO ENSURE EFFICIENT MANAGEMENT OF THE PROGRAMME. ?THE TOTAL ARTF COST OF MCP IS $30M OVER THREE YEARS</narrative>
  </description>
